The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Foreign coach for TFA soon
 FROM OUR CORRESPONDENT Jamshedpur: The Tata Football Academy (TFA) is recruiting a foreign coach soon. We havent decided on the man yet, but I can assure you that he will be from one of the top footballing nations, Satish Pillai, head of the TFA, said here on Sunday night. Ranjan Chowdhury and Carlton Chapman have been coaching the TFA boys for the last two seasons, while Vasant Singh is the physical trainer. The TFA boys would be visiting Germany in July to play a youth meet. The academy also plans to utilise AIFFs bilateral ties between India and Portugal, Pillai added. All 17 boys who graduated from the academy last season have been recruited by top Indian clubs.  Copyright 
